## Building a Combobox (search + select) in Vue 3

**Mental model:** A combobox is single-select: an input that filters a list and commits one value. The input reflects the selected option; reopening shows the full list. Track query, open state, and value separately; an outside click reconciles the input back to the committed label.

### Step 1 — Query, open, value
```vue
<script setup>
import { ref, computed } from 'vue';
const query = ref('');
const open = ref(false);
const value = ref(null);
</script>
```

### Step 2 — Filter while typing
```js
const filtered = computed(() => {
  const typing = open.value && query.value && (!value.value || query.value !== value.value.label);
  return typing
    ? props.options.filter((o) => o.label.toLowerCase().includes(query.value.toLowerCase()))
    : props.options;
});
```

### Step 3 — Commit a selection
```js
function select(o) { value.value = o; query.value = o.label; open.value = false; }
```

### Step 4 — Clear + outside-click reconcile
```js
function clear() { value.value = null; query.value = ''; }
function onDoc(e) { if (!root.value.contains(e.target)) { open.value = false; query.value = value.value ? value.value.label : ''; } }
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Reopen | Show all options. |
| Blur without select | Restore committed label. |
| No match | Empty-state row. |

**Interview tip:** Reconciling the input text to the committed value on blur is the combobox-specific detail (vs. a free autocomplete) — call out that the input is a *view of* the selected value, not independent state.

