## Building a Combobox (search + select) in Angular

**Mental model:** A combobox is single-select: an input that filters a list and commits one value. The input mirrors the selected option; reopening shows the full list; an outside click reconciles the text back to the committed label. Classic `NgModule` setup, no `?.`/`??` (the build rejects them), no `FormsModule`.

### Step 1 — Fields
```typescript
query = '';
open = false;
value: Option | null = null;
active = 0;
```

### Step 2 — Filter while typing (getter)
```typescript
get filtered(): Option[] {
  const typing = this.open && this.query && (!this.value || this.query !== this.value.label);
  if (!typing) { return this.options; }
  const q = this.query.toLowerCase();
  return this.options.filter((o) => o.label.toLowerCase().indexOf(q) !== -1);
}
```

### Step 3 — Commit / clear
```typescript
select(o: Option): void { this.value = o; this.query = o.label; this.open = false; }
clear(): void { this.value = null; this.query = ''; }
```

### Step 4 — Outside-click reconcile
```typescript
@HostListener('document:click', ['$event'])
onDoc(e: MouseEvent): void {
  if (!this.host.nativeElement.contains(e.target)) {
    this.open = false;
    this.query = this.value ? this.value.label : '';
  }
}
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Reopen | Getter returns all options. |
| Blur without select | Reconcile to committed label. |
| No match | Empty-state row. |

**Interview tip:** The reconcile-on-outside-click (input is a *view of* the committed value) is the combobox-specific behavior — `@HostListener('document:click')` + `contains` is the clean way to detect the outside click in Angular.

